    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Access to Taxis</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Alfred J Lurie letter on Betsy Wade's July 2 column nots wheelchair-accessible taxis are standard in all major British cities (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Betsy Wade's article on wheelchair-accessible taxicabs in many United States cities (''Fitting Taxis for Wheelchairs,'' July 2) didn't go far enough. All major cabs in British cities such as London, Glasgow, Edinburgh and Manchester are so equipped. No special vans for them. Just intelligently designed purpose-built taxis.</p>
        <p>ALFRED J. LURIE  New York, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
